Comparison of Major Collections
Feature	ArrayList	LinkedList	HashSet	TreeSet	HashMap
Ordered	Yes	Yes	No	Sorted	No
Duplicates	Yes	Yes	No	No	Keys No
Access Speed	Fast	Slow	Fast	Medium	Fast
Null Allowed	Yes	Yes	One Null	No	One Null Key
When to Use Which Collection?
ArrayList → Frequent data retrieval.
LinkedList → Frequent insertion/deletion.
HashSet → Unique elements with fast lookup.
TreeSet → Sorted unique elements.
HashMap → Fast key-value storage.
TreeMap → Sorted key-value storage.
PriorityQueue → Priority-based processing
